1
00:00:09,467 --> 00:00:11,900
<i>Our child is starting
chemotherapy.</i>

2
00:00:12,033 --> 00:00:14,367
<i> I can't handle this alone.</i>

3
00:00:14,500 --> 00:00:15,900
<i> I need you now.</i>

4
00:00:16,033 --> 00:00:17,133
<i> What do you want?</i>

5
00:00:17,267 --> 00:00:20,700
<i>A job, let me back into
Torrecampo Realty.</i>

6
00:00:20,833 --> 00:00:22,433
<i> If you don't,</i>

7
00:00:22,567 --> 00:00:24,667
<i>I'll expose that Ashley
is your daughter.</i>

8
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:27,233
<i>If you expose us,
it will destroy my family.</i>

9
00:00:27,367 --> 00:00:28,900
<i>But I'll still be a Torrecampo.</i>

10
00:00:29,033 --> 00:00:30,433
<i>You, though, where do you think
you'll end up?</i>

11
00:00:30,567 --> 00:00:32,367
<i> Hi, Mr. Lorenzo.</i>

12
00:00:32,500 --> 00:00:33,967
<i> I'm Thea.</i>

13
00:00:34,133 --> 00:00:35,267
<i> The young girl</i>

14
00:00:35,400 --> 00:00:38,367
<i>that my father used to pay off
his debts to you.</i>

15
00:00:43,067 --> 00:00:44,567
The girl...

16
00:00:45,300 --> 00:00:47,333
you kept photographing
over and over...

17
00:00:49,500 --> 00:00:52,267
<i> Hey, smile.</i>

18
00:00:54,833 --> 00:00:56,167
while you were abusing me.

19
00:01:00,400 --> 00:01:02,300
<i> You're beautiful, dear.</i>

20
00:02:15,633 --> 00:02:17,567
What do you need from me?

21
00:02:21,700 --> 00:02:25,600
I'm glad you're straightforward.

22
00:02:30,600 --> 00:02:32,267
I have something
I want you to do.

23
00:02:33,167 --> 00:02:34,500
And if you follow
my instructions...

24
00:02:35,800 --> 00:02:38,433
no one will ever know
what you did to me.

25
00:02:45,567 --> 00:02:49,533
Pao, you haven't been coming
here for days.

26
00:02:49,933 --> 00:02:54,667
I'm running out of excuses
whenever our child asks for you.

27
00:02:55,300 --> 00:02:56,567
I'm really sorry.

28
00:02:57,233 --> 00:02:58,833
The meetings have just been
nonstop.

29
00:03:00,633 --> 00:03:03,333
<i>We're still trying to broke
a deal with Mr. Lorenzo.</i>

30
00:03:04,367 --> 00:03:06,200
Love, I really want
to come there.

31
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:10,500
But I have so much
on my plate right now.

32
00:03:10,633 --> 00:03:12,700
But we need you, too.

33
00:03:13,767 --> 00:03:15,633
I'm struggling...

34
00:03:15,967 --> 00:03:18,900
Emotionally, physically,
mentally.

35
00:03:19,033 --> 00:03:21,000
<i> I'm exhausted, love.</i>

36
00:03:21,167 --> 00:03:23,267
<i>It feels like I have nothing
left to give.</i>

37
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:25,400
I need someone to lean on.

38
00:03:25,533 --> 00:03:28,400
Please, make some time for us.

39
00:03:29,433 --> 00:03:31,067
Please, just bear with me
a little longer.

40
00:03:31,933 --> 00:03:34,567
Once I fix everything here...

41
00:03:34,700 --> 00:03:37,100
Then you'll finally focus
on Jasmine and me?

42
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:39,933
<i>Love, you've said that
so many times.</i>

43
00:03:40,067 --> 00:03:42,067
How long are we supposed
to wait?

44
00:03:42,667 --> 00:03:43,700
Huh?

45
00:03:44,300 --> 00:03:45,333
Please.

46
00:03:45,467 --> 00:03:47,567
It feels like the company
matters more to you

47
00:03:47,700 --> 00:03:49,967
than your sick child.

48
00:03:51,167 --> 00:03:53,967
Marj, you know that's not true.

49
00:03:54,733 --> 00:03:56,100
<i> Then make us feel like</i>

50
00:03:56,233 --> 00:03:57,933
we're your priority.

51
00:03:58,500 --> 00:03:59,967
Jobert, what are you doing?

52
00:04:00,100 --> 00:04:02,467
Do you even know
how important this is?

53
00:04:04,133 --> 00:04:05,867
Marj, sorry.
I cannot do this right now.

54
00:04:06,500 --> 00:04:07,900
I have to go, bye.

55
00:04:11,867 --> 00:04:12,933
Hello?

56
00:04:20,567 --> 00:04:23,233
What are you doing?

57
00:04:23,367 --> 00:04:24,500
Why didn't you tell anyone,
Jobert?

58
00:04:24,633 --> 00:04:25,500
Gemma! Gemma!

59
00:04:25,633 --> 00:04:27,200
- What's going on here?
- Good Brother.

60
00:04:27,367 --> 00:04:28,733
- Jobert!
- Sir!

61
00:04:28,867 --> 00:04:31,533
Jobert shredded the original
signed contract

62
00:04:31,667 --> 00:04:34,567
for our Mandaluyong
project, Sir.

63
00:04:34,700 --> 00:04:38,400
It's due to be submitted to
the regulatory board tomorrow.

64
00:04:38,533 --> 00:04:40,700
I'm sorry, I'm really sorry.

65
00:04:40,833 --> 00:04:42,967
I didn't mean it, Good Bro.

66
00:04:43,100 --> 00:04:45,500
- I swear I didn't.
- Okay, okay.

67
00:04:45,633 --> 00:04:48,600
Print a new copy
of the contract.

68
00:04:48,733 --> 00:04:49,867
Then I'll sign it.

69
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:51,933
Send it right away
to Mrs. Alegre

70
00:04:52,067 --> 00:04:53,167
so she can sign it, too.

71
00:04:53,300 --> 00:04:54,900
And then, first thing
in the morning tomorrow,

72
00:04:55,033 --> 00:04:56,733
have it notarized

73
00:04:56,867 --> 00:04:58,400
so we can still meet the
submission deadline, okay?

74
00:04:58,533 --> 00:05:01,533
Sir, the problem is that
Mrs. Alegre is out of town.

75
00:05:01,700 --> 00:05:03,933
She's already in Iloilo.

76
00:05:04,067 --> 00:05:06,300
This is why you have to be
careful!

77
00:05:07,067 --> 00:05:09,433
Everyone here is already
stressed because of Mr. Lorenzo.

78
00:05:09,567 --> 00:05:10,600
And now you made it worse!

79
00:05:10,733 --> 00:05:12,400
I already apologized.

80
00:05:12,533 --> 00:05:14,233
Why are you still mad?

81
00:05:14,367 --> 00:05:18,633
- I'm not bad! I'm not bad!
- Jobert! Jobert!

82
00:05:18,767 --> 00:05:20,700
- Yes, yes.
- They said I'm bad!

83
00:05:21,500 --> 00:05:22,467
You're not bad, okay?

84
00:05:22,600 --> 00:05:24,067
You're not bad, Jobert.

85
00:05:24,200 --> 00:05:26,233
Okay, Calm down.

86
00:05:26,367 --> 00:05:27,400
Calm down.

87
00:05:27,533 --> 00:05:28,733
It's okay.

88
00:05:29,567 --> 00:05:31,100
Okay, you're not bad.

89
00:05:31,233 --> 00:05:34,700
No, no.
Jobert is not bad, okay?

90
00:05:35,333 --> 00:05:37,800
Okay now?
Book a flight to Iloilo.

91
00:05:37,933 --> 00:05:39,400
Send someone there

92
00:05:39,533 --> 00:05:41,667
to personally meet Mrs. Alegre.

93
00:05:43,033 --> 00:05:45,033
- But Sir.
- Gemma, just do it.

94
00:05:45,167 --> 00:05:46,233
Okay, Sir.

95
00:05:50,067 --> 00:05:51,133
Jobert.

96
00:05:51,267 --> 00:05:52,967
What? Are you okay?

97
00:05:53,100 --> 00:05:54,167
Are you okay?

98
00:05:55,500 --> 00:05:58,267
Good Bro, I'm sorry.

99
00:05:58,400 --> 00:06:00,933
I really didn't mean to.

100
00:06:01,067 --> 00:06:02,533
I didn't mean to.

101
00:06:02,667 --> 00:06:05,733
I was thinking
about Baby Jasmine.

102
00:06:06,267 --> 00:06:08,700
Poor Baby Jasmine.

103
00:06:08,867 --> 00:06:10,633
That's why I made a mistake.

104
00:06:10,767 --> 00:06:12,000
Sorry.

105
00:06:15,100 --> 00:06:16,867
Thank you for apologizing.

106
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:20,800
Don't worry about it anymore,
okay?

107
00:06:20,933 --> 00:06:22,567
We'll find a way to fix it.

108
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:26,067
- Oh...
- Okay?

109
00:06:26,800 --> 00:06:28,167
- Okay?
- Sorry.

110
00:06:28,300 --> 00:06:29,767
It's okay now.

111
00:06:30,967 --> 00:06:33,133
Who's going to believe you?

112
00:06:34,100 --> 00:06:36,400
You don't even have any
evidence.

113
00:06:39,633 --> 00:06:45,367
I even forgot to put an SD card
in the camera that day.

114
00:06:47,233 --> 00:06:48,767
You didn't forget.

115
00:06:50,667 --> 00:06:54,067
I took it while you were asleep.

116
00:07:06,333 --> 00:07:07,833
This is you, right?

117
00:07:13,233 --> 00:07:14,800
I knew it...

118
00:07:15,733 --> 00:07:18,667
this would come in handy
someday.

119
00:07:21,867 --> 00:07:23,033
And that's not all.

120
00:07:23,867 --> 00:07:25,633
I also have backups online.

121
00:07:26,733 --> 00:07:31,233
So you can't erase the horrible
thing you did to me.

122
00:07:34,167 --> 00:07:36,067
Choose, Mr. Lorenzo.

123
00:07:40,967 --> 00:07:42,900
Do what I tell you

124
00:07:44,467 --> 00:07:49,800
or watch your reputation
and your company fall apart.

125
00:07:52,700 --> 00:07:56,733
You might even lose your family.

126
00:07:58,500 --> 00:08:04,633
Not to mention, you could go
to prison for statutory rape.

127
00:08:11,867 --> 00:08:13,967
What do you want me to do?

128
00:08:17,467 --> 00:08:18,900
It's simple.

129
00:08:26,833 --> 00:08:28,900
Thanks, Good Brother.

130
00:08:29,767 --> 00:08:30,867
This is good.

131
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:33,500
That's my treat for you.
You did a good job at work.

132
00:08:34,067 --> 00:08:35,933
But next time, focus more, okay?

133
00:08:36,067 --> 00:08:37,600
So you don't make mistakes.

134
00:08:38,200 --> 00:08:40,067
I promise, Good Brother.

135
00:08:42,567 --> 00:08:43,967
- Good Bro.
- Oh?

136
00:08:44,633 --> 00:08:46,667
I have a request.

137
00:08:47,733 --> 00:08:48,767
Sure, what is it?

138
00:08:50,300 --> 00:08:51,767
Oh...

139
00:08:51,900 --> 00:08:55,400
Please don't tell my sister
what I did.

140
00:08:55,567 --> 00:08:56,800
Oh.

141
00:08:56,933 --> 00:08:59,533
I don't want her to get mad.

142
00:08:59,667 --> 00:09:02,367
I don't want her to know
I messed up.

143
00:09:04,333 --> 00:09:05,467
Okay, this stays between us.

144
00:09:05,600 --> 00:09:07,700
I won't tell your sister.

145
00:09:08,667 --> 00:09:11,467
I don't want to add
to her worries.

146
00:09:12,200 --> 00:09:13,600
She's already very stressed.

147
00:09:14,467 --> 00:09:16,433
Thank you, Good Brother.

148
00:09:17,900 --> 00:09:18,800
By the way,

149
00:09:18,933 --> 00:09:20,333
have you and your mom
visited Jasmine yet?

150
00:09:22,567 --> 00:09:23,867
Not yet.

151
00:09:26,233 --> 00:09:28,433
I'm scared.

152
00:09:28,600 --> 00:09:31,000
I don't know what to do.

153
00:09:31,133 --> 00:09:34,633
I might hurt Baby Jasmine again.

154
00:09:36,567 --> 00:09:37,800
Looks like we're the same.

155
00:09:40,133 --> 00:09:41,467
I'm completely clueless.

156
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:45,767
Sometimes I feel useless.

157
00:09:47,967 --> 00:09:49,867
Like everything I do just ends
up a failure.

158
00:09:52,167 --> 00:09:54,133
Sometimes I'm scared...

159
00:09:54,267 --> 00:09:58,500
scared I'll make a mistake
and hurt Jasmine.

160
00:10:00,433 --> 00:10:04,200
No, you're not a failure,
Good Brother.

161
00:10:04,367 --> 00:10:07,200
Look, you saved me.

162
00:10:07,333 --> 00:10:10,100
You'll save Baby Jasmine, too.

163
00:10:13,533 --> 00:10:14,767
I hope so.

164
00:10:17,167 --> 00:10:18,900
Thank you, Good Brother.

165
00:10:25,100 --> 00:10:26,033
Sir, excuse me.

166
00:10:26,167 --> 00:10:27,200
- Yes?
- She sent a message,

167
00:10:27,333 --> 00:10:29,233
Mr. Lorenzo's secretary.

168
00:10:30,100 --> 00:10:31,133
What did they say?

169
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:36,000
Mr. Lorenzo.

170
00:10:36,167 --> 00:10:37,267
Oh.

171
00:10:38,433 --> 00:10:41,033
Ay. I am so grateful
that you decided

172
00:10:41,167 --> 00:10:43,267
not to pull out
your investment sa company.

173
00:10:44,267 --> 00:10:45,233
Have a seat.

174
00:10:49,700 --> 00:10:51,433
You have no idea
what a relief this

175
00:10:51,567 --> 00:10:53,500
is for the company and our
employees.

176
00:10:53,633 --> 00:10:55,900
That's why I'm here
to personally thank you.

177
00:10:58,733 --> 00:11:03,700
Honestly, I didn't really want
to do this.

178
00:11:06,033 --> 00:11:09,267
But what changed your mind?

179
00:11:11,633 --> 00:11:13,367
Miss Villareal.

180
00:11:13,500 --> 00:11:14,800
Sorry, who?

181
00:11:15,833 --> 00:11:17,933
Actually, Mr. Lorenzo,

182
00:11:18,067 --> 00:11:21,600
he knows me as Mrs. Torrecampo.

183
00:11:21,733 --> 00:11:24,467
I'm Paolo's sister-in-law.

184
00:11:31,900 --> 00:11:34,000
Hey, why do you look
so surprised?

185
00:11:35,533 --> 00:11:37,000
I already told you,

186
00:11:37,133 --> 00:11:39,833
rejection isn't
in my vocabulary.

187
00:11:43,533 --> 00:11:46,233
So even if you push me away,
Paolo,

188
00:11:46,367 --> 00:11:49,800
I always manage
a dramatic comeback.

189
00:11:57,533 --> 00:11:59,567
Did Dr. Marquez call you?

190
00:12:00,467 --> 00:12:01,633
Yes.

191
00:12:01,767 --> 00:12:04,867
I spoke to him earlier.
He's in Singapore right now.

192
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:07,467
He's conducting
an experimental treatment

193
00:12:07,600 --> 00:12:09,667
for cases like Jasmine's.

194
00:12:10,300 --> 00:12:11,867
Would you allow Jasmine
to try it?

195
00:12:12,967 --> 00:12:16,667
Are you willing for her to
undergo experimental treatment?

196
00:12:16,833 --> 00:12:18,733
She's, she's a good candidate
for it.

197
00:12:19,633 --> 00:12:21,933
I still need to talk
to Paolo about it.

198
00:12:22,067 --> 00:12:25,367
Oh, yes, of course.

199
00:12:25,500 --> 00:12:28,033
You and Paolo need
to decide together.

200
00:12:29,333 --> 00:12:30,267
By the way, where is he?

201
00:12:30,400 --> 00:12:31,967
Because every time I visit here,

202
00:12:32,100 --> 00:12:33,533
you're the only one I see.

203
00:12:34,300 --> 00:12:35,800
Does he even visit Jasmine?

204
00:12:38,700 --> 00:12:40,833
Jas! Jas! Jas!

205
00:12:42,033 --> 00:12:43,633
Jas!

206
00:12:43,767 --> 00:12:45,633
- Call a nurse!
- Nurse! Nurse!

207
00:12:45,767 --> 00:12:46,800
Nurse!

208
00:12:48,433 --> 00:12:49,567
Jas!

209
00:12:49,700 --> 00:12:51,233
Sir, excuse me.

210
00:12:51,367 --> 00:12:52,400
Nurse, hurry!

211
00:12:54,567 --> 00:12:56,467
Put the patient
to side-lying position, now!

212
00:12:57,167 --> 00:12:59,233
I followed everything
you told me, Doc!

213
00:12:59,367 --> 00:13:02,367
I did all the safety measures.
Why did things get worse?

214
00:13:02,500 --> 00:13:04,333
Increase the oxygen to 15 LPM.

215
00:13:05,467 --> 00:13:07,500
Marj, Marj, don't blame
yourself.

216
00:13:07,867 --> 00:13:09,967
- You didn't...
- Give IV diazepam now!

217
00:13:14,433 --> 00:13:15,667
Move to cardiac monitor!

218
00:13:15,800 --> 00:13:16,833
Jas!

219
00:13:16,967 --> 00:13:18,600
Baby, please!

220
00:13:19,533 --> 00:13:20,800
Baby!

221
00:13:21,733 --> 00:13:22,900
Double time!

222
00:13:25,400 --> 00:13:27,367
Baby Jas...

223
00:13:46,600 --> 00:13:48,233
I'm just really curious,
Mr. Lorenzo.

224
00:13:49,500 --> 00:13:52,333
How exactly did Thea
convince you

225
00:13:52,467 --> 00:13:54,100
to stay and not pull
your investment

226
00:13:54,233 --> 00:13:55,500
on Torrecampo Realty?

227
00:13:59,133 --> 00:14:00,567
Let's just say...

228
00:14:01,467 --> 00:14:02,767
I owe her.

229
00:14:03,833 --> 00:14:05,233
So much.

230
00:14:05,367 --> 00:14:06,667
Me?

231
00:14:06,800 --> 00:14:09,667
Or do you mean my father?

232
00:14:10,667 --> 00:14:14,267
I guess Mr. Lorenzo owes
my father more than

233
00:14:14,400 --> 00:14:19,000
what he planned to invest
in your company.

234
00:14:21,333 --> 00:14:23,633
I just have to remind him of it.

235
00:14:29,267 --> 00:14:32,033
Anyway, I really have to go.

236
00:14:32,167 --> 00:14:34,700
Just deal with my people
from now on.

237
00:14:35,233 --> 00:14:36,367
Ah, thank you.

238
00:14:37,633 --> 00:14:38,933
Don't call me.

239
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:46,067
See?

240
00:14:46,200 --> 00:14:48,133
If it weren't for me,

241
00:14:48,267 --> 00:14:50,600
your company's problem
wouldn't be solved.

242
00:14:53,200 --> 00:14:56,233
Send me an invoice, and we'll
pay you.

243
00:14:56,933 --> 00:14:58,133
Wait.

244
00:14:58,933 --> 00:15:00,800
You know that's not
what I want, Paolo.

245
00:15:01,967 --> 00:15:02,967
Face it.

246
00:15:04,067 --> 00:15:05,467
You need me, too.

247
00:15:14,533 --> 00:15:15,933
Why don't you make a deal?

248
00:15:17,867 --> 00:15:20,333
If you hire me back
at your company...

249
00:15:22,600 --> 00:15:27,033
I promise to give you everything
you want.

250
00:15:41,400 --> 00:15:42,700
Hello, love?

251
00:15:46,467 --> 00:15:47,833
What?

252
00:15:55,467 --> 00:15:58,633
Look, Marj, I'm so sorry.

253
00:16:00,200 --> 00:16:02,400
I just met with Mr. Lorenzo.

254
00:16:03,600 --> 00:16:05,700
But don't worry.

255
00:16:06,567 --> 00:16:08,100
We already fixed the problem.

256
00:16:09,067 --> 00:16:12,133
Now I can help you...

257
00:16:12,267 --> 00:16:14,133
-That's enough, I don't want to
- Take care of Jasmine.

258
00:16:14,267 --> 00:16:15,133
I don't want to hear that
anymore.

259
00:16:15,267 --> 00:16:17,533
You've made that promise so many
times.

260
00:16:17,667 --> 00:16:20,033
Your company is what really
matters to you!

261
00:16:21,233 --> 00:16:23,267
Marj, I already explained
to you everything.

262
00:16:23,400 --> 00:16:25,933
Yes, I understand
it's important to you.

263
00:16:26,667 --> 00:16:29,600
So we can afford Jasmine's
treatment.

264
00:16:30,133 --> 00:16:32,467
But why does it feel like this?

265
00:16:33,300 --> 00:16:35,433
Like you just left me hanging.

266
00:16:35,733 --> 00:16:39,067
Like I'm the only one carrying
all this weight.

267
00:16:42,233 --> 00:16:44,667
Marj, this isn't only hard
for you.

268
00:16:45,433 --> 00:16:46,867
This is all too hard for me.

269
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:48,867
Every time I'm at work,

270
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:50,733
Jasmine is all I think about.

271
00:16:51,400 --> 00:16:54,300
It's not because I'm choosing
the company.

272
00:16:55,467 --> 00:16:57,033
You mean more to me than that.

273
00:16:58,933 --> 00:17:00,800
But I'm doing this

274
00:17:00,933 --> 00:17:03,600
because it's the only way I know

275
00:17:03,733 --> 00:17:06,833
to make sure Jasmine
still has a chance.

276
00:17:06,967 --> 00:17:08,867
But we need you!

277
00:17:09,567 --> 00:17:12,533
Your daughter needs you,
I need my husband.

278
00:17:13,267 --> 00:17:15,300
I'm trying, aren't I?

279
00:17:16,800 --> 00:17:18,700
Even when I'm exhausted,

280
00:17:18,833 --> 00:17:20,767
I still visit whenever I can.

281
00:17:21,467 --> 00:17:23,200
But whenever I'm here,

282
00:17:23,333 --> 00:17:26,100
all you do is criticize me.

283
00:17:26,233 --> 00:17:29,200
I can't even go near my daughter
because I might infect her.

284
00:17:30,367 --> 00:17:32,433
There's nothing I do right.

285
00:17:32,567 --> 00:17:33,933
Everything I do just ends up
a failure.

286
00:17:52,867 --> 00:17:55,267
And just because I'm not here...

287
00:17:56,633 --> 00:17:59,633
doesn't mean I'm not helping
you.

288
00:18:01,233 --> 00:18:03,333
Do you know your brother
made a huge mistake

289
00:18:03,467 --> 00:18:04,700
at the office earlier?

290
00:18:06,367 --> 00:18:09,067
But I already fixed it,
I didn't even tell you about it.

291
00:18:10,467 --> 00:18:12,333
Why? Because I know you're
stressed,

292
00:18:12,467 --> 00:18:14,067
and I didn't want
to add more to it.

293
00:18:15,233 --> 00:18:18,467
So now you're throwing that
in my face?

294
00:18:18,600 --> 00:18:21,133
Am I supposed to thank you
for that?

295
00:18:21,300 --> 00:18:24,700
Paolo, what our child is going
through is far worse.

296
00:18:24,833 --> 00:18:27,167
Right now, she needs both of us,
together and complete.

297
00:18:27,300 --> 00:18:28,333
But what are you doing?

298
00:18:28,467 --> 00:18:30,700
You keep avoiding us,
you always have an excuse.

299
00:18:32,100 --> 00:18:33,367
The way you're acting,

300
00:18:33,500 --> 00:18:34,900
it's like our child doesn't even
have a father.

301
00:18:35,033 --> 00:18:37,033
Like I don't even have a
husband.

302
00:18:42,500 --> 00:18:44,433
Let me guess.

303
00:18:44,567 --> 00:18:46,267
You just came from the hospital
again, right?

304
00:18:48,267 --> 00:18:50,533
Do you really have no plans
to start job hunting?

305
00:18:51,667 --> 00:18:55,400
Hon, I'm still applying
for jobs.

306
00:18:56,000 --> 00:18:57,933
But while I'm waiting to hear
back from companies,

307
00:18:58,067 --> 00:19:00,800
there's nothing wrong with
visiting Jasmine.

308
00:19:04,400 --> 00:19:08,200
Are you really visiting Jasmine?
Or Marj?

309
00:19:13,167 --> 00:19:15,567
Wait... why can't you answer?

310
00:19:18,333 --> 00:19:20,200
You still have feelings
for her, don't you?

311
00:19:24,267 --> 00:19:26,500
I may not be here all the time,

312
00:19:26,633 --> 00:19:30,533
but that doesn't mean
I'm neglecting you and Jasmine.

313
00:19:30,700 --> 00:19:32,733
Every day, I try to balance

314
00:19:32,867 --> 00:19:36,000
being a husband, a father,

315
00:19:36,133 --> 00:19:37,900
and a provider.

316
00:19:39,667 --> 00:19:41,867
But why does it feel like this?

317
00:19:42,567 --> 00:19:44,967
Like we're just an afterthought
to you?

318
00:19:45,100 --> 00:19:48,767
Like you only think about us
when everything else is done?

319
00:19:51,967 --> 00:19:55,400
Paolo, I don't feel like
we're partners anymore.

320
00:19:57,133 --> 00:20:00,233
Where are the promises you made
to me when you were courting me

321
00:20:00,367 --> 00:20:02,567
and when you married me?

322
00:20:08,567 --> 00:20:10,767
I don't want to be absent, Marj.

323
00:20:12,033 --> 00:20:13,833
But I also have the
responsibility

324
00:20:13,967 --> 00:20:15,867
to provide for our family

325
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:19,833
to ensure that Jasmine will get
the best medical treatment.

326
00:20:20,700 --> 00:20:26,100
And that responsibility involves
not being here all the time.

327
00:20:26,233 --> 00:20:28,500
Don't twist my helping Marj into
something else.

328
00:20:28,633 --> 00:20:29,867
You know what?

329
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:31,367
You have a really dirty mind.

330
00:20:32,467 --> 00:20:33,533
Why?

331
00:20:33,667 --> 00:20:36,400
What else am I supposed to think
about what you're doing?

332
00:20:37,300 --> 00:20:38,700
You can't even help
your own family,

333
00:20:38,833 --> 00:20:43,267
yet you're meddling in someone
else's problems?

334
00:20:44,167 --> 00:20:45,333
Why?

335
00:20:46,067 --> 00:20:47,333
Because you're such a nice guy?

336
00:20:48,700 --> 00:20:50,333
Just stop it, Edward.

337
00:20:51,067 --> 00:20:52,833
You know, Thea,
you think that way

338
00:20:52,967 --> 00:20:54,800
because you only help people

339
00:20:54,933 --> 00:20:56,200
when you need something
from them.

340
00:20:56,333 --> 00:20:58,400
Not everyone is like you, Thea!

341
00:21:00,600 --> 00:21:02,433
You've got some nerve!

342
00:21:08,867 --> 00:21:10,633
I can feel it
on my palm, Edward!

343
00:21:12,467 --> 00:21:15,400
Aren't you ashamed?
We're just living here for free,

344
00:21:15,533 --> 00:21:17,567
depending on your parents!

345
00:21:18,433 --> 00:21:20,567
And you still talk to me like
that?

346
00:21:22,933 --> 00:21:24,267
Remember this.

347
00:21:24,867 --> 00:21:27,667
I married you
because you promised

348
00:21:27,800 --> 00:21:30,367
you'd give me a good life.

349
00:21:31,167 --> 00:21:32,400
Ashley and me.

350
00:21:33,667 --> 00:21:37,567
But you keep messing
everything up.

351
00:21:39,100 --> 00:21:40,733
So in the end,

352
00:21:40,867 --> 00:21:43,600
I'm the one who has to fix
things for this family.

353
00:21:43,767 --> 00:21:45,400
What? Huh?

354
00:21:45,533 --> 00:21:46,700
What did you say?

355
00:21:47,100 --> 00:21:50,267
I'm not asking you to drop
everything.

356
00:21:52,033 --> 00:21:53,833
Paolo, we promised our child

357
00:21:53,967 --> 00:21:56,367
we wouldn't abandon her.

358
00:21:57,000 --> 00:21:59,667
You promised that you'll be
there for her.

359
00:22:00,867 --> 00:22:02,933
But every time
she looks for you,

360
00:22:03,067 --> 00:22:05,367
I'm forced to lie.

361
00:22:06,000 --> 00:22:09,267
Instead of giving her strength,
she just ends up disappointed.

362
00:22:15,267 --> 00:22:16,767
I don't know anymore.

363
00:22:18,433 --> 00:22:20,633
I don't know.

364
00:22:23,033 --> 00:22:25,300
One of these days,

365
00:22:25,433 --> 00:22:27,833
I'll be back
at Torrecampo Realty.

366
00:22:28,833 --> 00:22:29,833
Wait.

367
00:22:31,700 --> 00:22:34,533
I will never beg Paolo,

368
00:22:34,667 --> 00:22:35,600
especially not Dad,

369
00:22:35,733 --> 00:22:37,533
to take you back
into that company.

370
00:22:40,600 --> 00:22:43,500
Who told you I'd rely on you?

371
00:22:45,433 --> 00:22:47,400
After everything I did today...

372
00:22:49,067 --> 00:22:52,500
they'll be the ones kneeling
and begging me

373
00:22:52,633 --> 00:22:54,333
to come back to the company.

374
00:23:11,133 --> 00:23:14,300
I'm doing everything
I'm supposed to do.

375
00:23:16,100 --> 00:23:18,833
But it's still not enough
for you!

376
00:23:20,767 --> 00:23:22,800
I don't even know
where I stand anymore.

377
00:23:25,033 --> 00:23:27,600
Wait, wait.
You're leaving again?

378
00:23:29,800 --> 00:23:31,233
This won't be good for Jasmine

379
00:23:31,367 --> 00:23:33,500
if she sees us like this.

380
00:23:34,433 --> 00:23:36,200
She shouldn't see us fighting.

381
00:23:38,967 --> 00:23:40,100
I just need to cool off.

382
00:23:41,367 --> 00:23:42,733
I just need to cool off.

383
00:24:22,433 --> 00:24:23,833
- Sir.
- Oh?

384
00:24:24,600 --> 00:24:25,667
Dad.

385
00:24:30,033 --> 00:24:31,200
What's going on?

386
00:24:33,333 --> 00:24:34,600
Have a seat.

387
00:24:35,433 --> 00:24:37,167
You should know.

388
00:24:37,300 --> 00:24:39,800
Didn't Thea save
our entire project

389
00:24:39,933 --> 00:24:42,567
that heavily relied
on Mr. Lorenzo?

390
00:24:44,100 --> 00:24:46,800
I truly appreciate
your help, dear.

391
00:24:46,933 --> 00:24:49,333
I can't believe
you convinced Mr. Lorenzo

392
00:24:49,467 --> 00:24:52,200
not to pull out his investment.

393
00:24:52,333 --> 00:24:53,833
I truly thank you.

394
00:24:54,933 --> 00:24:57,067
Anything for the family...

395
00:24:58,000 --> 00:24:59,133
Dad.

396
00:24:59,800 --> 00:25:03,467
Ah, yes, I offered her
her consultancy fee...

397
00:25:04,633 --> 00:25:06,700
to show our gratitude
towards her, Dad.

398
00:25:06,833 --> 00:25:08,100
Are you serious?

399
00:25:08,233 --> 00:25:09,700
That's not gonna cut it!

400
00:25:10,233 --> 00:25:11,333
But, Dad...

401
00:25:12,367 --> 00:25:14,900
Thea is too valuable to lose.

402
00:25:17,600 --> 00:25:20,567
She's crucial to the success
of our company.

403
00:25:21,333 --> 00:25:24,467
That's why I want her back
immediately.

404
00:25:36,233 --> 00:25:39,300
Thank you for agreeing
to let me returns.

405
00:25:39,433 --> 00:25:42,133
I only agreed
because Dad asked me to.

406
00:25:42,667 --> 00:25:46,100
So, if we're in the office
together,

407
00:25:46,233 --> 00:25:47,667
let's just avoid each other.

408
00:25:48,533 --> 00:25:50,700
Seems a little late for that.

409
00:25:51,167 --> 00:25:53,033
I saw earlier

410
00:25:53,167 --> 00:25:57,833
how you were staring
at my cleavage.

411
00:25:57,967 --> 00:25:59,767
Don't you feel guilty for that?

412
00:25:59,900 --> 00:26:01,167
I know you did it on purpose.

413
00:26:01,300 --> 00:26:02,767
Why would I feel guilty?

414
00:26:02,900 --> 00:26:05,367
Edward's doing
his own mischief, too.

415
00:26:05,500 --> 00:26:08,400
I know he's not over Marj yet.

416
00:26:09,200 --> 00:26:10,167
What?

417
00:26:10,300 --> 00:26:11,933
I don't even understand Paolo
sometimes.

418
00:26:12,067 --> 00:26:14,467
I don't approve of him
prioritizing

419
00:26:14,600 --> 00:26:17,467
work problems over you
and Jasmine.

420
00:26:17,600 --> 00:26:21,467
As the father,
he should always be present.

421
00:26:21,600 --> 00:26:23,967
You draw your strength from him.

422
00:26:24,100 --> 00:26:25,000
I told you already.

423
00:26:25,133 --> 00:26:26,067
Don't mess with me.

424
00:26:26,200 --> 00:26:27,133
What's the matter?

425
00:26:27,267 --> 00:26:29,867
Are you scared
that if we work together,

426
00:26:30,000 --> 00:26:31,700
you'll get tempted again?
